{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_01Tim3sbux7sZQrZsnsSfF1t","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are met:\n\n- **app-producer** is `1/1 Ready`, no more CrashLoopBackOff.\n- **`/app` vhost** has `app-queue` (type `classic`) with messages flowing (5 and growing).\n- **Cluster** shows all 3 nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) running and healthy.\n\n**Root cause:** `app-user` had an empty `configure` permission regex on the `/app` vhost (write/read were `.*`, configure was blank), so the management-API `PUT /queues/%2Fapp/app-queue` call was rejected with `not_authorised`, causing the producer's script to exit and CrashLoop.\n\n**Fix:** granted `app-user` configure rights scoped to the exact queue name:\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \"^app-queue$\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\nThis is least-privilege (only lets the user declare/configure `app-queue`, not arbitrary topology), required no CRD/operator installation, and caused no data loss — the vhost, users, and existing cluster state were untouched."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":789,"cache_read_input_tokens":45886,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":789},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5731c15f-033c-49de-be07-e0c09e78da74","uuid":"c1208467-0cf7-439f-a9bc-641352ea5d91","request_id":"req_011CcaZf9BFYEVaGccBpNeBi"}
